{ A complex endgame from Horgen 1995 featuring mutual errors. Black draws with 1...Rf6!, attacking the h7-pawn and forcing either 2.Kxb2 Rb6+ (perpetual) or 2.Ra8+ Kxh7 3.Kxb2 Kg7 with equality. Both sides miss the decisive moves: Black's 1...Rb4?? abandons the key defensive file, and White's subsequent 3.Rc8+?? returns the king to h7 instead of the winning 3.Rc6!. The final moves show the classic technique of escorting a passed a-pawn with king and rook coordination against a lone defending rook. }
1... Rb4?? (1... Rf6! 2. Ra8+ (2. Kxb2 Rb6+ 3. Kc3 Rc6+ 4. Kb4 Rb6+ 5. Kc5 Rc6+ 6. Kd5 Rd6+) 2... Kxh7 3. Kxb2 Kg7) 2. Rc7 Ra4 3. Rc8+?? (3. a7?? Rxa7) (3. Rc6! Kxh7 4. Kxb2 Kg7 5. Kb3 Ra1 6. Kb4 Kf7 7. Kc5 Ke7 8. Kb6 Kd7 9. Kb7) 3... Kxh7 4. Rc6 Rb4?? (4... Kg7! 5. Kxb2 Kf7 6. Kb3 Ra1 7. Kb4 Ke7 8. Kb5 Kd7) 5. a7 Ra4 6. Rc7+ Kg6 7. Kxb2 Kf6 8. Kb3 Ra1 9. Kb4 Ke6 10. Kb5 Kd6 11. Rc6+ Kd5 12. Ra6 Rb1+ 13. Ka5 Kc5 14. Rc6+! Kxc6 15. a8=Q+ *


